org.easetech.easytest.converter

Class ConversionDelegator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.easetech.easytest.converter.ConversionDelegator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BaseConverter<List<Map<String,Object>>,List<org.junit.experimental.theories.PotentialAssignment>>

    public class ConversionDelegator
extends Object
implements BaseConverter<List<Map<String,Object>>,List<org.junit.experimental.theories.PotentialAssignment>>
    A Delegator class that is responsible for converting the raw data into user specified type. It implements the BaseConverter.convert(Object) method. It works as follows :
  • If the data is already converted by the user(lets say while loading from the Data Loader), it returns the data as it is.
  • If the data is not converted, it calls the registered converters one by one to convert the raw data into user specified format.
  • If still the data is not converted , it throws assertion failure exception
Author:
Anuj Kumar
